## Dereplicating the database - Dereplication is the reduction of a set of genomes based on high sequence similarity (e.g., >99% average nucleotide identity) between these genomes. This leads to reads being either randomly distributed across the redundant genomes, with a single random alignment reported from many possible options, or reported at all redundant locations. 

